  "text": "There are many ways to define poverty. None of them are perfect considering the soundness in theory and feasibility in practice. Here we use a food share based poverty line for estimating household subsistence. This poverty line is defined as the food expenditure of the household whose food expenditure share of total household expenditure is at the 50th percentile in the country [CITATION_1] . In order to minimize measurement error, we use the average food expenditures of households whose food expenditure share of total household expenditure is within the 45th and 55th percentiles of the total sample [CITATION_2] . Considering the economy scale of household consumption, the household equivalence scale is used rather than actual household size. The equivalence scale is:",
